\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T00:41:38.963Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"prompt\":\"## Code Review Request\\n\\n**What was implemented:** A new `perf` package providing span-based performance measurement API, replacing the old `LogDuration` pattern. The package provides hierarchical span tracking with automatic parent-child nesting via context propagation. Root spans emit a single DEBUG log line with the full timing tree. The spans are instrumented across hook_registry.go (root span), lifecycle.go (turn start/end handlers), strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go (PrepareCommitMsg, PostCommit), strategy/manual_commit_git.go (SaveStep), and strategy/manual_commit_push.go (PrePush).\\n\\n**Plan/Requirements:** Replace scattered `time.Now()` + `LogDuration()` calls with a structured span-based performance measurement system that:\\n1. Provides hierarchical timing (parent/child spans)\\n2. Emits a single log line per hook invocation with all substep timings\\n3. Supports error recording on spans\\n4. Uses context propagation for automatic nesting\\n\\n**BASE_SHA:** 9a14da7e3a0a36896be9e54ee9e7c3927873e741 (origin/main)\\n**HEAD_SHA:** 8cbc68bd37dfbee7751c95c705527e379db6752d\\n\\n**Description:** New `perf` package with Span API + instrumentation of all hook handlers and strategy methods with performance spans.\\n\\n**Files changed (9 files, +547 -46):**\\n- `perf/context.go` - Context key for span propagation\\n- `perf/span.go` - Core Span type with Start/End/RecordError/Measure\\n- `perf/span_test.go` - Unit tests for the perf package\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` - Replace LogDuration with root perf span\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry_test.go` - Update test to check for perf span log\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` - Add child spans to lifecycle handlers\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_git.go` - Add spans to SaveStep\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` - Add spans to PrepareCommitMsg and PostCommit\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go` - Add spans to PrePush\\n\\nPlease review these changes thoroughly. Look at the full diff by running:\\n```\\ngit diff 9a14da7e3a0a36896be9e54ee9e7c3927873e741...8cbc68bd37dfbee7751c95c705527e379db6752d\\n```\\n\\nAlso read the new files directly:\\n- perf/context.go\\n- perf/span.go  \\n- perf/span_test.go\\n\\nAnd read the changed files to see the full context:\\n- cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_git.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go\\n- cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go\\n\\nFocus on:\\n1. **Correctness:** Are spans always ended? Are there leak paths where End() is never called?\\n2. **API design:** Is the Span API well-designed? Are there footguns?\\n3. **Error handling:** Is RecordError used correctly? Are errors recorded before End()?\\n4. **Verbosity:** Is the instrumentation too granular? Too coarse?\\n5. **nolint removal:** Several `//nolint:nilerr` comments were removed - is this correct?\\n6. **Test coverage:** Are the tests sufficient?\\n7. **Performance:** Could the span overhead itself be a concern?\\n8. **Log output format:** Is the flat key format (steps.X_ms) good for querying?\\n\",\"agentId\":\"ac129d8ba23a9446b\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In `PostCommit`, `ctx` is the original context with the root span from `hook_registry.go`. All `perf.Start(ctx, ...)` calls in PostCommit create children of the root span. The `postCommitProcessSession` is called with the same `ctx`, and its internal spans also create children of root. This produces a flat tree with many siblings, which is exactly what the flat `steps.X_ms` output format supports.\\n\\nNow I have everything I need for a thorough review. Let me compile my findings.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# Code Review: Performance Span-Based Measurement System\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThis change introduces a new `perf` package that provides span-based performance measurement, replacing the old `LogDuration` pattern in `hook_registry.go`. The implementation is clean, well-tested, and achieves the stated goals. The root span in `executeAgentHook` collects all child spans from lifecycle handlers and strategy methods, emitting a single DEBUG log line per hook invocation.\\n\\n## What Was Done Well\\n\\n- **Clean API design**: The `Start` / `RecordError` / `End` trio is minimal and idiomatic. Context propagation for automatic parent-child nesting is the right choice.\\n- **Safety properties**: `End()` is idempotent (safe to call multiple times), `RecordError(nil)` is a no-op, and un-ended children are auto-ended by the parent. These eliminate common footguns.\\n- **Good test coverage**: The test suite covers root spans, nesting, idempotent End, auto-end children, Measure, RecordError (nil, first-wins, child error flag), and context propagation. All tests use `t.Parallel()`.\\n- **Minimal overhead**: Spans are lightweight struct allocations with `time.Now()` calls. No goroutines, no channels, no allocations beyond the span itself. This is appropriate for a CLI tool.\\n- **The `defer span.End()` pattern** in `hook_registry.go` is the right place for the root span -- it ensures the span always ends, even on panics.\\n- **The comment** about TTY confirmation not being wrapped in a span (line 448 of `manual_commit_hooks.go`) shows good judgment about what should and should not be timed.\\n\\n## Issues\\n\\n### Critical (Must Fix)\\n\\nNone. The committed code passes lint and all tests.\\n\\n### Important (Should Fix)\\n\\n**1. Discarded context creates misleading span names (overlapping siblings instead of parent-child)**\\n\\nIn `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`, at line 453:\\n\\n```go\\n_, saveStepSpan := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"build_and_save_step\\\")\\n```\\n\\nThe returned context is discarded. This means when `strat.SaveStep(ctx, stepCtx)` is called at line 495, the spans created inside `SaveStep` (`open_repository`, `load_session_state`, etc.) become **siblings** of `build_and_save_step`, not children. The `build_and_save_step` span and the SaveStep sub-spans overlap in time, which is confusing in output.\\n\\nThis pattern repeats throughout `lifecycle.go` -- every child span discards its context with `_`. There are two options:\\n\\n- **Option A (Recommended)**: Remove the wrapper spans like `build_and_save_step` since the SaveStep internals already have their own spans. The wrapper adds no information that the contained sub-spans don't already provide.\\n- **Option B**: Thread the context through by capturing it: `ctx, saveStepSpan := perf.Start(ctx, \\\"build_and_save_step\\\")`. This would make SaveStep's spans children of `build_and_save_step`. However, the current output format only renders one level of children, so deeper nesting would be invisible in logs -- making this option less useful without also updating the output format.\\n\\nThe same applies to the `PostCommit` and `postCommitProcessSession` flows in `manual_commit_hooks.go` where context is also discarded.\\n\\n**2. `RecordError` called with potentially nil error in `findSessionsForWorktree` early-exit path**\\n\\nIn `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`, at line 352-353:\\n\\n```go\\nif err != nil || len(sessions) == 0 {\\n    findSessionsSpan.RecordError(err)\\n```\\n\\nWhen `err == nil` and `len(sessions) == 0`, `RecordError(nil)` is called, which is a no-op. This is technically fine due to the nil guard in `RecordError`, but semantically the span ends without an error even though we took the early-exit path. The span correctly records \\\"no error\\\" since finding zero sessions isn't an error condition. This is acceptable but could be clearer with a comment. Not a bug, just a readability note.\\n\\n**3. Flat key format risks name collisions with duplicate span names**\\n\\nIf two child spans have the same name (e.g., two calls to `perf.Start(ctx, \\\"open_repository\\\")` in different code paths), the log output would have duplicate `steps.open_repository_ms` keys. In the current instrumentation, `SaveStep` in `manual_commit_git.go` has `open_repository` as a child span name, and `PostCommit` also has `open_repository_and_head`. The naming is currently careful enough to avoid collisions, but this is a latent risk worth documenting.\\n\\nRecommendation: Add a comment in `span.go` noting that child span names should be unique within a parent, or consider prefixing with the parent name.\\n\\n### Suggestions (Nice to Have)\\n\\n**4. `Measure` method is unused**\\n\\nThe `Measure` helper function (line 102 of `span.go`) is defined and tested but never used in any instrumentation site. All instrumentation uses the `Start`/`End` pattern directly. Consider removing it to reduce the API surface, or if it's intended for future use, add a comment indicating that.\\n\\n**5. The `perf` package depends on an internal package (`cmd/entire/cli/logging`)**\\n\\nThe `perf` package is a top-level module package that imports from `cmd/entire/cli/logging`. This inverts the typical dependency direction (top-level packages should be lower-level). While it builds fine and doesn't create import cycles today, it means `perf` cannot be used by any package that `logging` depends on. If `perf` needs broader reuse in the future, consider injecting the logger as a dependency rather than importing `logging` directly.\\n\\n**6. No test verifying the actual log output format**\\n\\nThe perf tests verify span state (duration, children, errors) but never verify the actual `logging.Debug` output. Consider adding a test that captures the slog output and verifies the flat key format (`steps.X_ms`, `steps.X_err`) is correct. This would catch regressions in the output format that the current state-based tests would miss.\\n\\n**7. Child span attrs are unused**\\n\\nChild spans can accept `attrs` via `Start(ctx, name, attrs...)`, but the `End()` method only emits attrs for the root span (line 93-96 of `span.go`). Child attrs are stored but never logged. Either document that child attrs are ignored, or remove the variadic parameter from child span creation to avoid confusion.\\n\\n**8. `nilerr` linter suppression comments removed but behavior unchanged**\\n\\nThe `//nolint:nilerr` comments were removed in `PrepareCommitMsg` and `PostCommit` where the code returns `nil` despite a non-nil `err`. The `RecordError(err)` call before `return nil` happens to break the `nilerr` pattern matcher, making the linter no longer detect the suppressed-error pattern. This is a subtle linter bypass. While the behavior is intentional (hooks must be resilient), the `nilerr` comments served as documentation that `nil` return was deliberate. Consider restoring them as documentation, e.g.:\\n\\n```go\\nopenRepoSpan.RecordError(err)\\nopenRepoSpan.End()\\nreturn nil //nolint:nilerr // Hook must be silent on failure\\n```\\n\\n**9. Uncommitted local change breaks the build**\\n\\nThe working tree has an uncommitted modification to `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/cmd/entire/cli/hooks_git_cmd.go` that replaces `time` import with `perf` import and changes the `gitHookContext` struct. This local change introduces a compile error (`undefined: time`). This appears to be work-in-progress for extending the span instrumentation to git hooks. If intended for this PR, it needs to be committed after fixing the compile error. If not, consider stashing it.\\n\\n## Plan Alignment\\n\\nThe implementation aligns well with the stated requirements:\\n\\n| Requirement | Status | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| Hierarchical timing (parent/child) | Met | Context propagation works. Output is flat (one level), which is appropriate for log querying. |\\n| Single log line per hook invocation | Met | Only root spans emit log output via `logging.Debug`. |\\n| Error recording on spans | Met | `RecordError` + `error` flag in output. |\\n| Context propagation for auto-nesting | Met | `contextWithSpan` / `spanFromContext` pattern. |\\n| Replace `LogDuration` in hook_registry | Met | Old pattern fully replaced with root span + `defer span.End()`. |\\n\\nThe granularity of instrumentation is appropriate -- major operations (open repo, load state, write checkpoint, etc.) each get a span, while trivial operations (string formatting, logging) do not. The decision to exclude TTY prompts from timing is documented and correct.\\n\\n## Relevant Files\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/perf/context.go` -- Context key for span propagation\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/perf/span.go` -- Core Span type implementation\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/perf/span_test.go` -- Unit tests\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` -- Root span creation\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` -- Lifecycle handler instrumentation\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_git.go` -- SaveStep instrumentation\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` -- PrepareCommitMsg/PostCommit instrumentation\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/performance-logging-investigation/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_push.go` -- PrePush instrumentation\"}],\"totalDurationMs\":1347777,\"totalTokens\":94539,\"totalToolUseCount\":47,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":536,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":91348,\"output_tokens\":2654,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\